.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "19 Dec 2025" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh reads commands from the user in a loop, executes built-in commands like "env", "ls", "exit", 
or launches external programs in subprocesses. It also handles environment variables, basic signal management
(e.g., CTRL+C), and searches the PATH for external commands.
The shell continues to prompt for command until the user exits.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
env
Prints the current environment variables.
.TP
exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
ls
Lists the contents of the current directory.
.TP
cd
Changes the current working directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
$ ./hsh
hsh$ env
PATH=/bin/ls
hsh$ cd /holbertonschool-simple_shell
hsh$ ls
README.md main.c main.h built_in_command.c env.c prompt.c search_path.c shell_env.c signal.c split_arg.c subprocess.c
hsh$ exit
